text.section:
As used in this section and KRS 281.874, unless the context otherwise requires:
"Certificate Type 01" means a private automobile;
"Certificate Type 02" means a taxicab or similar for-profit motor carrier vehicle;
"Certificate Type 03" means a bus service;
"Certificate Type 04" means a nonprofit transit system;
"Certificate Type 07" means a specialty carrier certified to transport nonemergency, ambulatory disoriented persons;
"Certificate Type 08" means a specialty carrier, using ramp or lift-equipped vehicles in compliance with the Americans with Disabilities Act, certified to transport nonemergency, nonambulatory persons;
"Level of eligibility" means the specialty transport classification a person is designated based upon the written recommendation of the person's personal physician, physician assistant, advanced practice registered nurse, or qualified mental health professional that is used to establish the type of specialty transport needed for the person; and
"Qualified mental health professional" shall have the same meaning as in KRS 202A.011.
